When the `binding` doesn't match the `activeLease`, a new `DispatchBinding` is created (which calls `lease.retain()`), and it replaces the old `binding` in the `ThreadLocal`. However, the old `binding` is never closed, so `lease.release()` is never called for the old lease. This causes the reference count of the old generation to never reach zero, preventing it from being closed and its ClassLoader from being garbage collected.

The fix should be to close the old binding before replacing it.
